main event: A radar-visual sighting of a white, round, high-speed object was reported in Dickinson, North Dakota on June 19, 1962.
interesting points: The object was tracked on radar and also visually observed by the radar operator for 2-3 minutes as it passed in front of the radar dome.
The object was described as moving in a straight line at high speed.
A follow-up investigation was mentioned, with the Technical Intelligence Center at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base potentially involved.
The report mentions other similar sightings and 'strange cargoes' that had appeared at the Technical Intelligence Center.
Additional details are provided, including the object's triangular shape, blue and white color, and its ability to change from moving to hovering.
